    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (71.69) and **Trea Turner** (70.89) anchoring the core, as both benefit from a combination of high-ceiling projections and favorable matchup dynamics against Pfaadt and Castillo. **Trea Turner** remains the primary engine for our scarcity-driven strategy; his ability to exploit the slow delivery of Pfaadt makes him a prime candidate for stolen base opportunities today, further bolstered by the leadoff spot. Meanwhile, **Kyle Schwarber** (65.10) rounds out a potent top-of-the-order stack, leveraging elite xwOBA metrics to offset a neutral platoon profile. **Colt Keith** (64.95) and **Logan O'Hoppe** (64.67) also provide strong value, with **Colt Keith** benefiting from a high-upside matchup against Junk and an advantageous 3rd-order position.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involved the bottom of the bench, where **Carson Benge** (36.95) and **Victor Scott II** (36.28) both failed to clear our 40.0 efficiency floor. While **Victor Scott II** offers the elite sprint speed we covet, the combination of a tough left-handed matchup against Suarez and a negative impact from the catcher's arm strength relegated him to the pine. **Carson Benge** fell just short of the cut, hampered by a L/L platoon disadvantage that eroded his base projection. Looking at the lineup, **Christian Yelich** (39.38) is currently positioned as our highest-risk start, barely scraping into the lineup. He faces a stiff test against Griffin (2.70 xERA), and we will be monitoring the late-inning situations closely; if the game environment shifts unfavorably, he is the first candidate to be pulled to preserve our game caps.",
